        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 4 at 11:11PM CDT by NWS Paducah KY</headline>
        <description>At 1110 PM CDT/1210 AM EDT/, Doppler radar was tracking strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from near Oakland City to near
Boonville to near St. Joseph. Movement was northeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Winslow, Dale, Santa Claus, Chrisney, Knottsville, Rockport,
Grandview, Owensboro, Tennyson, Folsomville, and Gentryville.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 165 between Mile Markers 68 and 70.
Interstate 64 in Indiana between Mile Markers 44 and 60.
Audubon Parkway between Mile Markers 21 and 23.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 400 AM CDT/500 AM EDT/ for
southwestern Indiana...and northwestern Kentucky.</instruction>
